    "text": [
        "Dear Jane,",
        "I hope this letter finds you well. I am glad that you have completed all the required courses in the high school. I am writing to share you some advice on the pre-med course at Queen\u2019s University.",
        "I took the pre-med course at university last year. This course includes several different subjects, including biology, organic chemistry, physics, Latin and medical English. The course is highly demanding, which involves lectures, seminars and group assignments. You are also required to attend laboratory sessions for biology and organic chemistry. Tutors will arrange for oral tests for Latin and medical English.",
        "I highly recommend that you could apply for the pre-med course at the Queen\u2019s University. The curriculum is well-organized, tutors are knowledgeable and extremely helpful. There is also opportunity to get an intership at the university research center. Most graduates from this course have been enrolled in the medical school.",
        "With regard to the application, I suggest that you could prepare for the personal statement and letter of recommendation. You could also find some useful tips for the interview online.",
        "I hope to hearing from you very soon. I wish you good luck in the application.",
        "Best regards,",
        "Ada"
    ],
